## ExpectInterface interface


<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
export interface ExpectInterface 
```

## Methods

|  Method | Description |
|  --- | --- |
|  [a(type)](./earljs.expectinterface.a.md) | Matches an instance of the provided class or primitive type. Examples:<!-- -->1. <code>expect.a(MyClass)</code> - matches <code>new MyClass</code>, but not <code>new Other()</code> 2. <code>expect.a(String)</code> - matches <code>&quot;foo&quot;</code>, but not <code>123</code> |
|  [anything()](./earljs.expectinterface.anything.md) | Matches any value. |
|  [arrayOfLength(length)](./earljs.expectinterface.arrayoflength.md) | Matches an array containing exactly given number of items. |
|  [arrayWith(items)](./earljs.expectinterface.arraywith.md) | Matches an array containing the provided items. |
|  [containerWith(items)](./earljs.expectinterface.containerwith.md) | Matches an iterable containing the provided items. |
|  [numberCloseTo(target, options)](./earljs.expectinterface.numbercloseto.md) | Matches numbers that are close to the target value. The options are used to specify the maximum difference.<!-- -->The range is \[expected - delta, expected + delta\] (inclusive). |
|  [numberGreaterThan(target)](./earljs.expectinterface.numbergreaterthan.md) | Matches a number greater than target. |
|  [numberGreaterThanOrEqualTo(target)](./earljs.expectinterface.numbergreaterthanorequalto.md) | Matches a number greater than or equal to target. |
|  [numberLessThan(target)](./earljs.expectinterface.numberlessthan.md) | Matches a number less than target. |
|  [numberLessThanOrEqualTo(target)](./earljs.expectinterface.numberlessthanorequalto.md) | Matches a number less than or equal to target. |
|  [objectWith(subset)](./earljs.expectinterface.objectwith.md) | Matches an object containing given key-value pairs. |
|  [stringMatching(substring)](./earljs.expectinterface.stringmatching.md) | Matches strings that contain the provided substring. |
|  [stringMatching(pattern)](./earljs.expectinterface.stringmatching_1.md) | Matches strings that conform to the provided pattern. |
